{
  "text": "In particular, we use the topological relationships described in [CITATION_1] ; examples of such operators are the relations Equal, Inside, Touch, Meet, among others. Given a trajectory Tj and a region Ri, the operator opi returns a boolean value B \u2261 {true, f alse} whether the trajectory Tj and the region Ri satisfy the topological relationship opi (e.g., an Inside operator will be true if the trajectory was sometime inside region Ri during time interval inti). For simplicity in the following we assume that the spatial operator is set to Inside and it is thus omitted from the query examples.",
  "citation_candidates": [
